result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamie L. Delebreau #570188 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent/Deliver Narcotics [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Conspiracy to Commit], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(a).
  • Possess w/ Intent/Deliver Narcotics [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Conspiracy to Commit], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Habitual Criminality], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Habitual Criminality], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: court orders DNA sample but not duplicated and DNA surcharge $250.00 due while incarcerated and while on ES.  In addition, on this case, court orders any & all necessary DOC supervision fees due during ES.
court orders defendant obtain or maintain full time employment or part time employment if enrolled in school. court orders defendant obtain HSED/GED or high school diploma.

court orders No contact with co-defendants Samantha Smith & Margaret Towns.  court orders No contact with any of the victims or their families, No contact with Three Lakes Pharmacy (Oneida Co), Wall St Pharmacy Eagle River (Vilas Co) and Laona Pharmacy (Forest Co).  court orders defendant not to be in company of any person who is using, purchasing or possessing illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.

court orders Absolute sobriety to include No purchase, possession or consumption any alcohol or controlled substances unless prescribed by physician & then only according to physician's orders. Defendant to advise DOC of any & all prescribed medications and all prescriptions shall be verified by DOC agent.  court orders AODA assessment followed by treatment & aftercare, participate in Cognitive Thinking Program and COMPAS evaluation including vocational & educational needs.  Enter into, participate in & successfully complete any assessments, evaluations and/or treatment programs as directed by DOC agent.
